# 1. Data Files (Never upload large datasets or generated data to GitHub!)
*.csv
*.xlsx
*.npz
processed_cancer_data.npz

# 2. Jupyter Notebook Auto-Saves (Prevents messy commit histories)
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# 3. Python Cache (Useless machine-code files your computer generates to run faster)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# 4. Virtual Environments (Massive folders that others should install themselves)
venv/
env/
.venv/

# 5. Editor Settings (Keeps your personal VS Code colors/settings off GitHub)
.vscode/
.DS_Store